  "text": "The Grafana database migration framework lives entirely in `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrator/`. The 9 core source files are: (1) **migrator.go** \u2014 the migration runner (`Migrator` struct) with `RunMigrations`/`run`/`doMigration`/`exec` execution chain, the `MigrationLog` version tracking struct (mapped to the `migration_log` table), `AddCreateMigration` which creates the tracking table, `InTransaction` which handles rollback on error via `sess.Rollback()`, and advisory locking via `casRestoreOnErr`. (2) **dialect.go** \u2014 the `Dialect` interface (SQL dialect abstraction with Lock/Unlock/CreateDatabaseFromSnapshot etc.), `BaseDialect` base implementation, `NewDialect` factory, and `LockCfg`. (3) **mysql_dialect.go** \u2014 `MySQLDialect` implementing MySQL-specific SQL generation, locking (GET_LOCK/RELEASE_LOCK), error handling. (4) **postgres_dialect.go** \u2014 `PostgresDialect` with PostgreSQL-specific SQL, advisory locks (pg_try_advisory_lock), upsert, ordering. (5) **sqlite_dialect.go** \u2014 `SQLite3` dialect for SQLite. (6) **types.go** \u2014 `Migration` and `CodeMigration` interfaces, `Table`/`Index`/`Column` type constants. (7) **migrations.go** \u2014 concrete migration types (`MigrationBase`, `RawSQLMigration`, `AddColumnMigration`, `AddTableMigration`, `DropTableMigration`, etc.). (8) **conditions.go** \u2014 `MigrationCondition` interface and condition implementations for conditional migration execution. (9) **column.go** \u2014 `Column` struct definition used by all migration types.",
